Discover K in the group model¶

Using stick-breaking to construct a dirichlet process. Max K should be smaller than sample size

In [3]:
# function to fit a group model without a-priori k
# maxk is the dirichlet T parameter
def discover_k_grp(target,dtype,auto,maxk):
    tm.K = maxk
    tm.mtype = 'grp'
    tm.target = target # 'self','targ','avg'
    tm.dtype = dtype # 'norm','raw'
    tm.auto = auto # 'noauto','all'
    tm.stickbreak = True
    tm.optim = pyro.optim.Adam({'lr': 0.0005, 'betas': [0.8, 0.99]})
    tm.elbo = TraceEnum_ELBO(max_plate_nesting=1)
    #dynamically initiate data
    dt = globals()['t{}_{}_{}_3d'.format(target,dtype,auto)]
    #fit the model
    seed,mapp,mem,lp = tm.tomtom_svi(dt)
    return seed, mapp, mem, lp

Visualizing modeling outcome¶

1) First identify meaningful clusters based on some criterion.

Here we threshold the fitted mixture weight, adjust in the tomtom_utils script

2) Check how well the model describes the data in a singel cluster

First use the fitted model params to generate data for a single cluster. Plot generated data against real data assigned to that same cluster

This allows us to see whether the data are well modeled by the family of distributions we chose

For each transition pair, calculate the mean pairwise KL divergence across all meaningful clusters, then sort outcome by mean ks
